an outside perspective

00:14:47.960 --> 00:14:50.200
either from an
educational specialist,

00:14:50.200 --> 00:14:52.719
or convening a group of
alums from a course that

00:14:52.719 --> 00:14:54.510
are five years out,
that you might actually

00:14:54.510 --> 00:14:56.850
run into an airport,
are two practical ways

00:14:56.850 --> 00:14:59.675
that we talked about to try
to crystallize those enduring

00:14:59.675 --> 00:15:00.300
understandings.

00:15:00.300 --> 00:15:04.440
We were all really taken by
that part of the aim idea.

00:15:04.440 --> 00:15:08.320
We talked about posting
learning objectives

00:15:08.320 --> 00:15:10.870
in the physical
classroom environment,

00:15:10.870 --> 00:15:13.720
and/or in some electronic
way checking in with students

00:15:13.720 --> 00:15:16.090
every one to two weeks to
say, like, how far along

00:15:16.090 --> 00:15:16.987
are we progressing?

00:15:16.987 --> 00:15:18.820
I know that's getting
a little bit into some

00:15:18.820 --> 00:15:21.700
of the more assessing
things, but just making sure

00:15:21.700 --> 00:15:23.710
that you're continuously
revisiting the learning

00:15:23.710 --> 00:15:25.630
objectives as opposed to
writing them and putting them

00:15:25.630 --> 00:15:27.379
aside, or putting them
on your first slide

00:15:27.379 --> 00:15:28.690
and putting them aside.

00:15:28.690 --> 00:15:29.470
Wonderful.

00:15:29.470 --> 00:15:32.890
One thing I'm struck by about
aim is how ambitious, sort of,

00:15:32.890 --> 00:15:36.550
the airport goal is, and
that less can often be more

00:15:36.550 --> 00:15:39.530
of this idea of everything
seems important,

00:15:39.530 --> 00:15:43.694
but then nothing gets sort of
the treatment that it deserves.

00:15:43.694 --> 00:15:46.360
And I think these schematics are
very interesting to think, sort

00:15:46.360 --> 00:15:48.640
of how much are we trying
to do, and how much they

00:15:48.640 --> 00:15:49.850
relate to each other.

00:15:49.850 --> 00:15:51.705
So even if we don't
give them to students,

00:15:51.705 --> 00:15:53.830
how do we ourselves understand
how these things all

00:15:53.830 --> 00:15:54.471
fit together?

00:15:54.471 --> 00:15:54.970
Great.

