00:16:22.150 --> 00:16:24.310
One theme that came
up with our group

00:16:24.310 --> 00:16:27.550
is the importance of building
trust in your community,

00:16:27.550 --> 00:16:29.650
and making sure that
the students know

00:16:29.650 --> 00:16:32.080
that it's OK to ask questions.

00:16:32.080 --> 00:16:36.550
And also we discuss how
it's great to empower

00:16:36.550 --> 00:16:38.800
the students to decide
themselves how are

00:16:38.800 --> 00:16:40.480
we going to build a community.

00:16:40.480 --> 00:16:43.810
And that will help with detect.

00:16:43.810 --> 00:16:46.250
Another topic that
we talked about was

00:16:46.250 --> 00:16:49.930
the power of small group
discussions and presentations

00:16:49.930 --> 00:16:54.700
and how that peer effect can
be motivating to help students

00:16:54.700 --> 00:16:57.190
prepare and do the
reading, or whatever work

00:16:57.190 --> 00:16:59.050
is needed before class.

00:16:59.050 --> 00:17:02.980
And if they don't do the
work or reading, that one,

00:17:02.980 --> 00:17:05.920
they need to be able to own it
and acknowledge it when they're

00:17:05.920 --> 00:17:08.599
doing small group
work, and secondly,

00:17:08.599 --> 00:17:12.670
that they may be motivated to
do that work because they know

00:17:12.670 --> 00:17:15.010
that their peers are depending
on them to contribute

00:17:15.010 --> 00:17:18.339
to that small group work.

00:17:18.339 --> 00:17:21.420
We also talked
about cases in which

00:17:21.420 --> 00:17:24.849
students need to
self-evaluate their own work.

00:17:24.849 --> 00:17:27.819
And it was related
that students are often

00:17:27.819 --> 00:17:31.090
very highly critical of
themselves, and maybe

00:17:31.090 --> 00:17:34.390
one of that, this was
in the case of speaking,

00:17:34.390 --> 00:17:37.120
that the students
may be self-critical

00:17:37.120 --> 00:17:39.790
because they don't realize
the huge amount of effort that

00:17:39.790 --> 00:17:42.910
goes into preparing
presentations or speeches.

00:17:42.910 --> 00:17:45.400
And it would be great to
be transparent about that

00:17:45.400 --> 00:17:48.340
so that they know how much
time it takes and then we'd

00:17:48.340 --> 00:17:51.730
have a better gauge about
how to self-evaluate where

00:17:51.730 --> 00:17:53.890
they are currently
in their skills

00:17:53.890 --> 00:17:56.600
and how they can improve.

00:17:56.600 --> 00:17:58.780
We also talked
